<chapter id="part23">
<title>User's Guide Part 2 and 3</title>
<para>This concludes Part 1 of the User's Guide to operating &celestia;.  In Part 2, you will learn what image files are, how &celestia; loads and uses them, and how data files of various kinds are used to instruct &celestia; in what to do and where to do it.  Part 2 will teach you how to modify those data files and locate and download scores of other add-on files designed by &celestia; users.  These files include exotic spacecraft, fictional solar systems, rotating black holes and much more.  Obtaining and using some of them will significantly boost your viewing pleasure in the &celestia; universe.</para>

<para>Part 3 of the User's Guide will teach you how to create scripts which are a series of lists that &celestia; follows one at a time to take a space journey.  For example, you can design a script to open &celestia; not at Io but orbiting a Red Giant star thousands of light years away.  Then as you watch, your spacecraft will accelerate and fly back to Earth at warp speed.  You can also insert text messages for the viewer to read.  The Run Demo referenced earlier in this Guide is just such a script journey.</para>


</chapter>

